## Watch Command Special Case
The watch command needs to stream events, so device.rs watch function needs to accept the output trait:

```rust
// In device.rs
pub fn watch_buttons_with_output(
    device: &Device,
    output: &dyn Output,
    once: bool,
    timeout_secs: u64,
) -> Result<(), SdError> {
    loop {
        match device.inner.read_input(Duration::from_millis(50)) {
            Ok(Some(StreamDeckInput::ButtonStateChange(states))) => {
                for (key, &pressed) in states.iter().enumerate() {
                    if pressed {
                        let event = ButtonEvent {
                            key: key as u8,
                            pressed: true,
                            timestamp_ms: current_timestamp_ms(),
                        };
                        output.button_event(&event);

                        if once {
                            return Ok(());
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
            _ => {}
        }
    }
}
```

